    <text id="B2016T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Lawson and the other Methodist Episcopal Church Trustees ask Brackett to use his
                    influence to have John Scott reappointed as teacher.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Chaplain R. M. Manly<lb/>State <abbr
                            expan="Superintendent">Supt.</abbr> Freedmens Schools</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-09-30"><abbr expan="September">Sept.</abbr> 30th 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>We the undersigned Trustees, Pastor and Officers of the Colored <abbr
                        expan="Methodist Episcopal">M. E.</abbr> Church of Staunton <abbr
                        expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr> have the honor to inform you that on the 24th
                    inst. we forwarded a Petition to the <abbr
                        expan="American Missionary Association">A.M.A.</abbr> to have Mr. John Scott
                    (who was here in the Winter of 1866) returned to this place the coming season.
                    We also beg leave to state that at a meeting of the Colored people held for
                    considering this subject that the sense of the people was taken and the whole
                    body with one single exception voted in favor of forwarding this Petition.</p>

                <p>And now thinking that you may have an influence in this matter we must earnestly
                    pray that you will so direct it as to return Mr. Scott to us.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>Rev. E. Lawson - preacher in charge<lb/>Trustees Aaron
                        <unclear>Shoaly</unclear><lb/>Francis Overton<lb/>Aderson King<lb/>Wm
                        Denny<lb/>Oscar Morris<lb/>David Davenport</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
